WEBVTT

00:02.460 --> 00:05.922
{\an8}IN A MIDDLE SCHOOL FULL
OF BULLIES, INSANE TEACHERS,

00:06.005 --> 00:09.217
{\an7}AND GROSS SCHOOL LUNCHES,
NED BIGBY--THAT'S ME--

00:09.300 --> 00:12.429
{\an7}AND MY 2 BEST FRIENDS
TRY TO DO THE IMPOSSIBLE,

00:12.512 --> 00:14.681
{\an8}CREATE A GUIDE THAT WILL
HELP YOU SURVIVE SCHOOL.

00:14.764 --> 00:18.852
{\an8}♪ COMING UP,
LOOKING OUT ♪

00:18.935 --> 00:22.105
{\an8}♪ I'LL SURVIVE IT
NO DOUBT ♪

00:22.188 --> 00:25.108
{\an8}♪ NEVER FEAR,
BRING IT ON ♪

00:25.191 --> 00:28.445
{\an7}♪ BREAK IT DOWN,
WHAT'S IN MY WAY? ♪

00:28.528 --> 00:34.534
{\an7}♪ AND I...I'M FINDING
MY PLACE IN THIS WORLD ♪

00:34.617 --> 00:36.453
{\an8}♪ AND I... ♪

00:36.536 --> 00:37.537
{\an7}"NED'S DECLASSIFIED
SCHOOL SURVIVAL GUIDE."

00:37.620 --> 00:41.916
{\an8}YOUR RESULTS MAY VARY.

00:42.000 --> 00:44.127
WHEN WILL THIS
COLD WEATHER END?

00:44.210 --> 00:45.962
I LOVE COLD, DAMP DAYS.

00:46.045 --> 00:49.716
{\an1}SPEAKING OF WHICH,
LATER TODAY IN SCIENCE,

00:49.799 --> 00:52.302
{\an1}WE'RE ALL GOING TO LEARN
ABOUT WEATHER PATTERNS

00:52.385 --> 00:54.888
AND HOW A SHIFT
IN THE JET STREAM

00:54.971 --> 00:57.807
{\an1}COULD DRAMATICALLY
CHANGE THE WEATHER...

00:57.891 --> 00:59.309
VERY, VERY QUICKLY.

00:59.392 --> 01:02.812
OH, NO.

01:02.896 --> 01:06.858
EVERYBODY RELAX,
TAKE IT EASY, CALM DOWN,

01:06.941 --> 01:09.486
OR YOU'RE GOING
TO GET--AAH!

01:24.250 --> 01:27.128
IF YOU HAVE THE IRRESISTIBLE
URGE TO GET OUTSIDE,

01:27.212 --> 01:29.506
YOU MAY HAVE
SPRING FEVER.

01:29.589 --> 01:31.007
OTHER SYMPTOMS
TO LOOK OUT FOR ARE

01:31.090 --> 01:33.384
{\an4}A LONGING TO BE CLOSE
TO THOSE YOU WANT
TO BE CLOSER TO...

01:33.468 --> 01:35.678
{\an1}JENNIFER,
YOU LOOK RADIANT.

01:35.762 --> 01:37.347
AND MY BACKPACK
IS FILTHY.

01:37.430 --> 01:38.848
I'VE GOT TO
CLEAN IT.

01:38.932 --> 01:40.934
AND THE NEED TO GET RID
OF A WINTER'S WORTH OF CLUTTER

01:41.017 --> 01:42.644
WITH SOME SPRING-CLEANING.

01:42.727 --> 01:44.479
{\an8}AND ONE WAY
TO REDUCE THE FEVER

01:44.562 --> 01:45.897
{\an8}IS TO ASK YOUR TEACHER
TO HAVE CLASS OUTSIDE.

01:45.980 --> 01:47.941
CAN WE HAVE HOMEROOM
OUTSIDE TODAY?

01:48.024 --> 01:49.943
[STUDENTS CHEERING]

01:50.026 --> 01:51.861
NO! I'M NOT SUPPOSED TO,

01:51.945 --> 01:55.323
{\an1}BECAUSE VICE-PRINCIPAL
CRUBBS SAID...

01:55.406 --> 01:57.534
NO ONE IS GOING
OUTSIDE TODAY.

01:57.617 --> 02:00.370
WHY? BECAUSE DURING LAST YEAR'S
OUTBREAK OF SPRING FEVER,

02:00.453 --> 02:02.914
YOU ALL RAN OUTSIDE,
AND 9 DIDN'T COME BACK...

02:02.997 --> 02:04.374
FOR A WEEK!

02:04.457 --> 02:07.669
SO THIS SCHOOL
IS IN LOCKDOWN MODE.

02:07.752 --> 02:09.545
SHOO, SHOO, SHOO!

02:09.628 --> 02:12.799
{\an1}PUT AN EGG IN YOUR SHOE
AND SPLIT, BEAT IT.

02:14.300 --> 02:16.553
I GOT THE FEVER!
I'VE GOT TO GET OUTSIDE BEFORE

02:16.636 --> 02:19.347
{\an1}ANOTHER COLD FRONT COMES IN
AND...WHAT'S WITH THE CALENDAR?

02:19.430 --> 02:20.515
I'VE BEEN ON LISA'S
WAITING LIST FOR MONTHS,

02:20.598 --> 02:22.892
AND TODAY'S THE DAY

02:22.976 --> 02:25.562
{\an5}I GET TO SPEND SECOND,
FOURTH, AND SIXTH
PERIOD WITH HER.

02:25.645 --> 02:27.522
AND BY THE END
OF THE DAY,

02:27.605 --> 02:28.898
SHE'LL HAVE
COOKIE FEVER.

02:28.982 --> 02:31.776
{\an1}YOU'VE GOT TO HELP ME
GET OUTSIDE!

02:32.569 --> 02:34.696
{\an1}WHAT ARE YOU SO DEEP
IN THOUGHT ABOUT?

02:39.701 --> 02:43.162
[AHEM] UH...

02:43.246 --> 02:44.873
JENNIFER.

02:44.956 --> 02:46.457
WALK WITH ME TO CLASS?

02:51.379 --> 02:53.256
SO, WHAT'S IT
GOING TO BE?

02:53.339 --> 02:55.133
DO YOU WANT TO GO
WITH ME OR FAYMEN?

02:56.217 --> 02:58.177
I CAN'T DECIDE!

02:58.261 --> 03:01.764
...WHAT TO CLEAN.
SPRING IS HERE.

03:05.560 --> 03:09.063
AN UNLOCKED WAY
OUTSIDE. LATER.

03:09.147 --> 03:10.773
I GOT THE FEVER!

03:10.857 --> 03:13.026
KISS ME, NED BIGBY!

03:13.109 --> 03:15.695
GET TO CLASS, BIGBY.
NOW!

03:16.487 --> 03:17.906
AAH!

03:17.989 --> 03:20.783
YOU WILL KISS ME!

03:22.118 --> 03:25.663
{\an1}OK. TIME TO SPEND
A GORGEOUS SPRING DAY

03:25.747 --> 03:28.875
WITH THE GIRL OF MY--

03:30.501 --> 03:31.794
WHOA!

03:31.878 --> 03:33.963
THE POLLEN COUNT
IS REALLY HIGH,

03:34.047 --> 03:36.174
AND MY ALLERGY MEDICINE
ISN'T WORKING.

03:36.257 --> 03:39.802
{\an5}THIS IS THE ONLY
HYPOALLERGENIC
OUTFIT I HAVE LEFT.

03:39.886 --> 03:41.304
[SNIFFS]

03:41.387 --> 03:42.055
BUT I'M
LOOKING FORWARD

03:42.138 --> 03:45.224
TO SPENDING THE DAY
WITH YOU, SIMON.

03:45.308 --> 03:50.980
[AH-CHOO!]

03:51.064 --> 03:52.815
ME, TOO.

03:54.359 --> 03:55.944
HI.

03:56.027 --> 03:58.112
{\an1}FAYMEN, YOU ARE
SO SWEET.

03:59.072 --> 04:01.199
AND MY LOCKER
IS SO DIRTY.

04:01.282 --> 04:03.534
{\an1}AND SPRING IS
A TIME FOR CLEANING.

04:03.618 --> 04:06.913
{\an5}BUT IN MY COUNTRY,
SPRING IS A TIME
FOR KISSING.

04:06.996 --> 04:07.622
AAH!

04:07.705 --> 04:10.333
MY EYES! MY EYES!

04:10.416 --> 04:12.460
{\an1}MY EYES!

04:14.420 --> 04:15.380
[SIREN]

04:22.762 --> 04:24.681
BOY, DO THEY
HAVE THE FEVER.

04:24.764 --> 04:25.431
CAN I HAVE
THE BATHROOM PASS?

04:34.774 --> 04:36.192
JUST FOLLOW THE MAP,

04:36.275 --> 04:39.320
AND YOU'LL BE OUTSIDE
IN A FLASH. HA HA HA.

04:45.451 --> 04:46.577
AAH!

04:46.661 --> 04:48.788
{\an1}GET BACK HERE, NED BIGBY!
I WILL KISS YOU TODAY!

04:48.871 --> 04:50.915
GORDY! GORDY! SHE'S UP HERE!
SHE'S UP HERE!

04:50.999 --> 04:54.711
AAH! AAH!

04:54.794 --> 04:57.547
AH...SPRING FEVER.

04:57.630 --> 04:59.048
[CAT SNARLS]

04:59.132 --> 05:01.300
{\an1}THIS IS A WONDERFUL
LOCKDOWN PICNIC, SIMON.

05:01.384 --> 05:02.301
[SNIFFS]

05:02.385 --> 05:05.555
CARE FOR SOME GUAVA?

05:05.638 --> 05:08.057
[AH-CHOO!]

05:08.141 --> 05:10.560
AREN'T YOU HAVING ANY?

05:13.646 --> 05:15.356
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

05:23.531 --> 05:25.324
J--JENNIFER...

05:25.408 --> 05:27.160
{\an1}THIS DESIRE
OF YOURS TO CLEAN

05:27.243 --> 05:29.370
{\an1}MIGHT BE YOUR WAY
OF AVOIDING A PROBLEM.

05:29.454 --> 05:30.997
WELL, PPPTTT.

05:31.080 --> 05:33.916
{\an1}NOW, IS THIS
A WOOD SHOP PROBLEM

05:34.000 --> 05:37.920
{\an1}OR A RELATIONSHIPPY
BOY-KISSY-GIRLIE PROBLEM?

05:38.004 --> 05:40.173
THE SECOND ONE.

05:40.256 --> 05:42.800
AH. WELL, IN THAT CASE...

05:43.718 --> 05:45.261
I HAVE A PROBLEM!

05:45.344 --> 05:47.013
LISA'S ALLERGIES ARE BACK,

05:47.096 --> 05:49.265
AND NOW SHE'S ALL SNIFFLY
AND BUGGERY AGAIN.

05:49.348 --> 05:51.350
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO.

05:51.434 --> 05:52.602
OK, BUT REMEMBER,

05:52.685 --> 05:54.687
{\an1}IT'S WHAT'S INSIDE A PERSON
THAT REALLY MATTERS.

05:54.771 --> 05:56.647
YOU MEAN, LIKE,
ALL HER MUCUS?

05:56.731 --> 06:00.109
{\an1}NO, I MEAN BEAUTY IS
IN THE EYE OF THE BEHOLDER.

06:01.277 --> 06:03.279
LISA! LISA!

06:03.362 --> 06:05.531
{\an1}SIMON, WHERE
HAVE YOU BEEN?

06:05.615 --> 06:07.825
{\an1}IS EVERYTHING
ALL RIGHT?

06:11.037 --> 06:14.040
EVERYTHING'S JUST FINE.

06:15.083 --> 06:17.418
LET'S GO. UH!

06:19.587 --> 06:22.632
[ELECTRICAL CRACKLING]

06:22.715 --> 06:23.591
{\an1}YOU DONE
WITH THAT, MA'AM?

06:23.674 --> 06:26.052
NO! I'VE--

06:26.135 --> 06:27.136
NED?

06:27.220 --> 06:30.348
{\an1}I GOT TO GET OUTSIDE,
FEEL THE WARM SUN

06:30.431 --> 06:31.808
ON MY DISGUISED FACE.

06:31.891 --> 06:32.558
{\an1}PLUS I'M HIDING
FROM MISSY.

06:32.642 --> 06:33.476
{\an1}SO, DO YOU WANT
TO GO OUT WITH ME?

06:33.559 --> 06:35.394
WHOA!

06:35.478 --> 06:37.897
{\an1}DO YOU WANT TO GO OUT?
YOU AND ME?

06:37.980 --> 06:40.316
TOGETHER? GOING OUT?

06:40.399 --> 06:42.401
I...I...

06:44.570 --> 06:46.364
I CLEAN.

06:53.079 --> 06:55.540
{\an1}WHERE DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE GOING?

06:55.623 --> 06:57.542
OH!

06:57.625 --> 06:58.459
[KISS KISS]

06:59.669 --> 07:02.296
{\an1}JUST ONE KISS!
ONE KISS!

07:02.380 --> 07:05.007
ALL RIGHT, GUYS.
REMEMBER TO CLEAN UP.

07:05.091 --> 07:07.009
I'LL TAKE CARE
OF IT.

07:07.093 --> 07:08.386
[WHIRRING]

07:14.767 --> 07:15.852
[WHIRRING STOPS]

07:15.935 --> 07:17.353
ALL RIGHT.
THIS ISN'T MY FORTE,

07:17.436 --> 07:21.607
BUT IS THIS ABOUT
THE GOOFY MOP-HEADED ONE

07:21.691 --> 07:23.359
OR THE FOREIGN ONE?

07:23.442 --> 07:25.194
BOTH. I'M CONFUSED.

07:25.278 --> 07:27.989
I REMEMBER WHEN I
WAS IN SCHOOL

07:28.072 --> 07:29.031
AND LIKED 2 GIRLS
AT THE SAME TIME,

07:29.115 --> 07:31.784
DIDN'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

07:31.868 --> 07:34.370
{\an1}SO I BUILT 38 BIRDHOUSES
IN ONE DAY.

07:34.453 --> 07:37.206
{\an1}ONE WAS OAK,
ONE WAS MAPLE,

07:37.290 --> 07:40.001
AND ONE WAS PINE.

07:40.084 --> 07:41.210
ANYWAY, IN THE END,
I REALIZED THAT

07:41.294 --> 07:43.045
MY PROBLEMS
WOULD NOT GO AWAY

07:43.129 --> 07:45.464
BY BUILDING
BIRDHOUSES.

07:47.592 --> 07:48.843
RIGHT.

07:48.926 --> 07:49.886
{\an1}AND I CAN'T MAKE
MY PROBLEMS GO AWAY

07:49.969 --> 07:52.388
BY SPRING-CLEANING.

07:52.471 --> 07:55.600
{\an1}MAYBE THE NED FIREWORKS
WERE JUST IN MY HEAD.

07:55.683 --> 07:57.810
{\an1}MAYBE FAYMEN JUST NEEDS
KISSING LESSONS.

07:57.894 --> 07:59.687
MAYBE YOU SHOULD GO
TALK TO THEM.

08:04.317 --> 08:05.151
MR. CHOPSAW--

08:05.234 --> 08:07.403
{\an1}YOU NEED TO KISS BETTER.
TRY LIP-UPS.

08:07.486 --> 08:09.030
LIP-UPS?

08:09.113 --> 08:11.199
YEAH, LIP-UPS.

08:12.450 --> 08:14.285
HAVE YOU SEEN NED?

08:14.368 --> 08:15.828
OR FAYMEN? MOSTLY NED.

08:15.912 --> 08:16.871
Lisa: SIMON?

08:16.954 --> 08:18.789
SIMON?

08:18.873 --> 08:20.583
[SIGHS]

08:25.922 --> 08:28.090
I CAN'T HELP IT.
I'M SHALLOW.

08:28.174 --> 08:30.176
{\an4}LOOK, LISA IS ONE
OF THE SWEETEST GIRLS
IN THIS SCHOOL.

08:30.259 --> 08:32.595
{\an1}SO DON'T CONCENTRATE
ON HER LOOKS.

08:32.678 --> 08:36.182
{\an5}CONCENTRATE ON ALL
THE WONDERFUL THINGS
SHE'S DONE FOR YOU.

08:47.735 --> 08:49.528
OK, I MADE THOSE UP.
BUT LISA WOULD DO

08:49.612 --> 08:51.447
THOSE THINGS FOR ME
IF I DESERVED IT.

08:51.530 --> 08:53.991
AND HOTTIE OR SNOTTY,
SHE'S THE GIRL FOR ME,

08:54.075 --> 08:56.953
AND I'M GOING TO
TELL HER.

08:57.036 --> 08:59.997
{\an1}AND I HAVE TO TELL NED
HOW I FEEL.

09:02.541 --> 09:04.377
[BELL RINGS]

09:04.460 --> 09:05.544
[KISSING]

09:05.628 --> 09:07.630
[BACK-UP ALARM BEEPING]

09:07.713 --> 09:09.215
I'M DOING LIP-UPS.

09:09.298 --> 09:11.133
{\an1}RIGHT.

09:11.217 --> 09:12.510
[SCREECH]

09:12.593 --> 09:15.346
FINALLY! GYM!
TIME TO GO--

09:15.429 --> 09:16.639
INSIDE.

09:16.722 --> 09:17.807
WE'RE HAVING A PHYSICAL
FITNESS TEST TODAY.

09:17.890 --> 09:20.268
INDOORS!

09:22.061 --> 09:26.857
GYM...INDOORS? NO WAY.

09:30.069 --> 09:33.656
[LAUGHING HYSTERICALLY]

09:38.119 --> 09:39.412
NED! NED! NED!

09:39.495 --> 09:42.999
BIGBY, GET DOWN
FROM THERE! BIGBY!

09:43.082 --> 09:44.166
GET DOWN FROM THERE!

09:44.250 --> 09:46.502
I'M GOING TO MAKE IT!

09:49.547 --> 09:51.507
[THUD]

09:51.591 --> 09:54.176
LISA!

09:54.260 --> 09:57.346
LISA...HEY,
YOU LOOK GREAT.

09:57.430 --> 09:59.598
{\an1}MY MOM DROPPED OFF
MY NEW MEDICINE AND CLOTHES,

09:59.682 --> 10:01.267
AND BYE-BYE ALLERGIES.

10:01.350 --> 10:03.561
{\an1}AND WHERE HAVE YOU
BEEN ALL DAY?

10:03.644 --> 10:06.022
I HAD A PROBLEM,
BUT I'M BETTER NOW,

10:06.105 --> 10:07.565
AND I CAN'T WAIT
TO SPEND

10:07.648 --> 10:09.358
THE REST OF SIXTH
PERIOD WITH--

10:09.442 --> 10:10.026
[BELL RINGS]

10:10.109 --> 10:12.445
YOUR TIME'S UP, COOK.

10:12.528 --> 10:15.656
{\an1}NOW I GET TO CARRY
LISA'S BOOKS TO CLASS.

10:15.740 --> 10:17.533
SORRY, SIMON.

10:19.327 --> 10:21.037
[SOBBING]

10:21.120 --> 10:23.706
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

10:23.789 --> 10:25.207
FOR THE LAST TIME,

10:25.291 --> 10:26.876
EVERYBODY GET AWAY
FROM THAT WINDOW!

10:26.959 --> 10:28.294
AND NO CLASS OUTSIDE!

10:28.377 --> 10:29.879
WHY NOT?

10:29.962 --> 10:31.422
YEAH!

10:29.962 --> 10:31.422
YEAH!

10:31.505 --> 10:33.799
AS A MAN OF SCIENCE,
YOU SHOULD KNOW

10:33.883 --> 10:35.384
THAT THE SUN'S
ULTRAVIOLET RAYS

10:35.468 --> 10:37.720
CAUSE THE BODY
TO PRODUCE VITAMIN D,

10:37.803 --> 10:39.764
WHICH IS IMPORTANT TO DEVELOP
STRONG BONES AND TEETH.

10:39.847 --> 10:41.974
YEAH!

10:39.847 --> 10:41.974
YES, I KNEW THAT.

10:42.058 --> 10:45.186
{\an1}AND YOU KNOW HOW QUICKLY
THE WEATHER PATTERNS CHANGE.

10:45.269 --> 10:47.063
{\an1}SO, DO YOU WANT TO DENY
THE MOST COMPLEX LIFE FORM

10:47.146 --> 10:48.397
WHAT IT NEEDS TO SURVIVE--

10:48.481 --> 10:51.233
WARM, SUNNY,
WINTER-ENDING WEATHER?!

10:51.317 --> 10:52.526
YEAH!

10:51.317 --> 10:52.526
YEAH!

10:52.610 --> 10:53.903
[SIREN]

10:53.986 --> 10:54.904
I SMELL THE FEVER.

10:54.987 --> 10:58.324
{\an1}DO SOMETHING TO CONTROL
YOUR CLASS BETTER, SWEENEY.

10:59.408 --> 11:02.787
{\an1}CLASS, TODAY WE'RE GOING TO
LEARN ABOUT THE WEATHER!

11:02.870 --> 11:06.040
AND THE BEST WAY
TO DO THAT...

11:06.123 --> 11:08.417
IS TO HAVE CLASS OUTSIDE!

11:08.501 --> 11:10.127
[STUDENTS CHEERING]

11:14.256 --> 11:16.384
[SIREN WAILS WEAKLY]

11:21.514 --> 11:22.890
NED BIGBY!

11:22.973 --> 11:24.934
I GOT THE FEVER!

11:28.687 --> 11:31.607
{\an1}AH. ONE SPRING-FEVER
KISS CAN'T HURT.

11:31.690 --> 11:34.652
NED, I HAVE TO
TELL YOU SOME--

11:37.988 --> 11:39.615
NEVER MIND.

11:39.698 --> 11:40.991
{\an1}JENNIFER.

11:42.993 --> 11:45.871
BETTER.

11:45.955 --> 11:46.789
I DO LIP-UPS.

11:46.872 --> 11:50.334
WHOO!

11:50.418 --> 11:56.215
{\an1}AH. THIS WEATHER SURE WARMS
MY BROKEN, SHALLOW HEART.

11:58.676 --> 12:01.303
OK. THAT'S ENOUGH.

12:01.387 --> 12:03.139
{\an1}♪ WHY'D YOU MAKE IT
SO COMPLICATED? ♪

12:03.222 --> 12:05.683
♪ WHOA-OA-OA ♪

12:07.059 --> 12:08.519
HI, EVERYBODY!
I'M BACK...

12:08.602 --> 12:11.897
{\an1}FROM MY YEAR OF LIVING
WITH THE PENGUINS.

12:11.981 --> 12:15.109
{\an1}AND THE FIRST THING I'M DOING
IS REBUILDING THE "HOWLER."

12:15.192 --> 12:16.944
THERE HASN'T BEEN A NEW EDITION
SINCE I LEFT.

12:17.027 --> 12:18.779
ALL RIGHT!
WHO'S WITH ME?

12:21.240 --> 12:24.493
NEWSPAPER? FORGET IT.
WRITING BAD.

12:24.577 --> 12:26.787
STOP IT. YOU HAVE
NO POWER OVER ME.

12:26.871 --> 12:28.622
WHAT ABOUT THE POWER
OF THE PRESS?

12:28.706 --> 12:30.166
YOU COULD RUN
THE "HOWLER"

12:30.249 --> 12:31.792
{\an5}AND SHAPE AND MOLD
THE THOUGHTS
OF HUNDREDS.

12:31.876 --> 12:33.544
{\an1}THE PEN IS MIGHTIER
THAN THE SWORD,

12:33.627 --> 12:34.545
{\an1}AND THE NEWSPAPER IS
THE MIGHTIEST SWORD OF ALL!

12:34.628 --> 12:38.507
{\an5}TAKE CHARGE FOR ONCE
IN YOUR LIFE,
NED BIGBY.

12:38.591 --> 12:42.011
ARE YOU A MAN
OR A MOUSE?

12:42.094 --> 12:44.638
MR. MONROE, I'M READY
TO GET MY HANDS DIRTY

12:44.722 --> 12:45.764
WITH THE INK OF FREEDOM!

12:45.848 --> 12:46.265
ANY MORE VOLUNTEERS?

12:46.348 --> 12:49.101
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

12:50.186 --> 12:53.606
{\an5}I DON'T WANT TO
WRITE FOR THE STUPID
SCHOOL NEWSPAPER.

12:53.689 --> 12:55.691
WRITING BAD.

13:06.702 --> 13:08.537
{\an1}YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE A WRITER
TO WORK ON THE SCHOOL NEWSPAPER,

13:08.621 --> 13:11.499
BECAUSE IT'S
A SCHOOL NEWSPAPER.

13:11.582 --> 13:13.209
{\an7}IT'S WHERE YOU LEARN TO BE
A WRITER, PHOTOGRAPHER,

13:13.292 --> 13:15.544
{\an8}DESIGNER, WHATEVER.

13:15.628 --> 13:17.713
SO JUMP ON BOARD
AND HAVE FUN.

13:17.796 --> 13:19.924
{\an1}AND NO ONE IS MORE INFORMED
THAN THE NEWSPAPER STAFF.

13:22.092 --> 13:23.969
[BELLS RINGING LOUDLY]

13:24.053 --> 13:26.972
AAH!

13:27.640 --> 13:30.392
{\an1}AND GET YOUR FRIENDS
TO HELP OUT,

13:30.476 --> 13:33.020
EVEN WHEN THEY
DON'T WANT TO.

13:33.103 --> 13:33.896
{\an1}I NEED
GOOD REPORTERS,

13:33.979 --> 13:36.565
{\an1}AND YOU'RE GOOD
AT ASKING TOUGH QUESTIONS.

13:36.649 --> 13:38.234
{\an1}AND YOU TRICKED ME
INTO THIS.

13:38.317 --> 13:38.943
FINE!

13:41.654 --> 13:43.739
I'M GOING TO ASK YOU
ONE MORE TIME!

13:43.822 --> 13:47.243
DO YOU WANT TO GO
FOR PIZZA TONIGHT?

13:47.326 --> 13:48.577
COOKIE'S BUSY.
HE JUST STARTED

13:48.661 --> 13:50.246
WRITING FOR THE
SCHOOL NEWSPAPER.

13:50.329 --> 13:52.206
OH, YEAH?
WHAT ARE YOU WRITING?

13:52.289 --> 13:54.458
WELL, I'M WRITING...

13:56.544 --> 13:58.879
I'M WRITING HOROSCOPES.

13:58.963 --> 14:00.339
{\an1}WHAT BETTER WAY
TO GET YOUR FORTUNE

14:00.422 --> 14:01.173
THAN FROM A COOKIE?

14:01.257 --> 14:04.510
OH! GO ON.

14:04.593 --> 14:06.470
{\an1}THANKS FOR COVERING
FOR ME.

14:06.554 --> 14:09.181
OH, I WASN'T
COVERING.

14:10.808 --> 14:13.269
OK. MOZE, YOU'RE
OUR STAR REPORTER.

14:13.352 --> 14:15.896
{\an1}I'LL DO PHOTOGRAPHY, SINCE
THERE'S NO WRITING INVOLVED.

14:15.980 --> 14:18.941
COCONUT HEAD AND SETH,
YOU BE MY LAYOUT GUYS.

14:19.024 --> 14:20.442
GREAT!

14:20.526 --> 14:22.611
STUDENTS, THIS IS
MR. HAL E. BURTON,

14:22.695 --> 14:24.738
CHAIRMAN
OF THE SCHOOL BOARD.

14:24.822 --> 14:29.368
{\an5}HE'S IN CHARGE
OF ALL THE MONEY
THE SCHOOL GETS.

14:29.451 --> 14:30.619
SO BE NICE.

14:32.538 --> 14:36.041
{\an1}SCHOOL NEWSPAPERS.
THEY'RE A WASTE OF FUNDS.

14:36.125 --> 14:37.751
GREAT.

14:37.835 --> 14:38.586
NOW I'M OFF
TO A MEETING

14:38.669 --> 14:41.797
{\an1}FOR THE NEW ADDITION
I'M BUILDING.

14:41.880 --> 14:43.632
OH. AFTER YOU,
YOUR HONOR.

14:43.716 --> 14:44.883
HA HA HA...

14:47.386 --> 14:48.637
[BELL RINGS]

14:48.721 --> 14:50.264
HERE'S
THE HOROSCOPE PAGE.

14:50.347 --> 14:52.975
{\an1}"GEMINI--HOP
TO CLASS TODAY."

14:53.058 --> 14:55.060
HOW DO YOU DO IT?

14:55.144 --> 14:57.438
I MAKE EVERYTHING UP.

14:58.063 --> 15:00.691
HEY, DON'T PUT
MY NAME ON IT.

15:00.774 --> 15:03.444
I DON'T WANT ANYONE TO KNOW
I'M WRITING THAT JUNK.

15:03.527 --> 15:06.697
{\an4}OK. SO, WHAT'S
THIS WEEK'S HEADLINE
BREAKING NEWS STORY?

15:06.780 --> 15:09.241
MR. SWEENEY
GOT A NEW HAMSTER.

15:09.325 --> 15:11.368
{\an1}37 STUDENTS GOT SICK
AFTER LUNCH THIS PAST WEEK,

15:11.452 --> 15:15.247
AND NOBODY KNOWS WHY.

15:16.915 --> 15:17.541
DON'T ASK ABOUT
ALL THAT BARFING.

15:17.625 --> 15:21.086
I WAS TOLD TO KEEP
MY MOUTH SHUT.

15:22.129 --> 15:23.213
{\an3}[AHEM]

15:23.297 --> 15:24.423
{\an3}PLEASE?

15:24.506 --> 15:25.591
OK, CHECK THIS OUT.

15:25.674 --> 15:27.968
THE SCHOOL BOARD
MADE US SWITCH

15:28.052 --> 15:29.678
TO A NEW FRUIT VENDOR.

15:29.762 --> 15:32.681
THEY'RE CHEAPER,
BUT WOULD YOU EAT THESE?

15:36.435 --> 15:37.311
THE NEW "HOWLER"
IS A HIT!

15:37.394 --> 15:40.856
{\an1}NOW WE'VE GOT TO FIND
OUR NEXT BIG NEWS STORY.

15:40.939 --> 15:41.774
AAH!

15:41.857 --> 15:44.568
NED, LOOK OUT!
AH, TOO LATE.

15:44.652 --> 15:45.861
LOOSE CEILING TILES.

15:45.944 --> 15:47.446
I WAS SUPPOSED
TO FIX THEM,

15:47.529 --> 15:49.740
BUT I NEVER GOT THE MONEY
FOR THE SUPPLIES.

15:49.823 --> 15:52.368
OH! AH!

15:53.744 --> 15:56.497
THIS SORT OF MUCKRAKING
WILL NOT BE TOLERATED.

15:59.291 --> 16:00.542
THE BUDGET IS TIGHT,

16:00.626 --> 16:03.253
{\an1}AND THE SCHOOL BOARD HAS
NON-FRUIT-RELATED EXPENSES

16:03.337 --> 16:06.465
{\an1}TO WORRY ABOUT...
LIKE THE NEW ADDITION.

16:06.548 --> 16:08.467
[SNAPS FINGERS]

16:08.550 --> 16:12.262
{\an5}CAN'T WE MOVE
THE WATER HEATER
OVER THERE?

16:12.346 --> 16:13.222
YOU HEARD MR. BURTON.

16:13.305 --> 16:15.474
ANY MORE BAD NEWS,
AND IT'S DETENTION FOR YOU

16:15.557 --> 16:18.310
AND NO JOB FOR HIM...

16:18.394 --> 16:19.144
FOR LIFE!

16:22.648 --> 16:24.191
[HAMSTER SQUEAKING]

16:24.274 --> 16:25.901
THERE'S YOUR NEW HEADLINE--

16:25.984 --> 16:29.655
"SWEENEY'S GOT
A NEW RAT-THING."

16:30.864 --> 16:32.741
{\an1}THE RAT-THING STORY.
I LIKE THAT.

16:32.825 --> 16:34.535
{\an1}AND I LIKE YOU,
CRUBBS.

16:34.618 --> 16:36.120
{\an1}COME ON OVER
TO THE HOUSE FOR DINNER,

16:36.203 --> 16:38.706
AND WE'LL TALK
ABOUT A RAISE.

16:38.789 --> 16:40.040
{\an3}AH...

16:45.587 --> 16:48.048
{\an1}MISSY, ARE YOU
A GEMINI?

16:48.132 --> 16:49.842
YEP, AND I'M HOPPING
TO MY CLASS

16:49.925 --> 16:52.594
JUST LIKE MY
HOROSCOPE SAID. BYE.

16:55.013 --> 16:56.432
Moze: THIS IS IT?

16:56.515 --> 16:58.434
THIS IS OUR NEXT BIG
NEWS BREAKING STORY?

16:58.517 --> 17:00.102
IT'S THE BEST WE GOT
WITHOUT GETTING US

17:00.185 --> 17:00.769
IN TROUBLE
WITH CRUBBS.

17:00.853 --> 17:03.897
{\an1}HEY, OUR FREE SPEECH
IS PROTECTED

17:03.981 --> 17:05.816
{\an1}BY THE STATUE
OF LIBERTY.

17:05.898 --> 17:08.277
{\an5}WELL, UNLESS
ANOTHER STORY
FALLS FROM THE SKY,

17:08.359 --> 17:10.570
MARMADUKE IS IT.

17:10.654 --> 17:11.613
AAH!

17:17.953 --> 17:19.371
HOROSCOPES ARE GREAT.

17:19.454 --> 17:22.833
{\an1}SO I'M DOING A SPECIAL
"HOWLER" HOROSCOPE EXTRA.

17:24.209 --> 17:25.711
"LEO--BEAT UP
LOOMER TODAY."

17:25.794 --> 17:28.589
{\an1}I DON'T KNOW
HOW HE DOES IT.

17:35.554 --> 17:39.141
"MEET ME AFTER FOURTH PERIOD
FOR THE REAL STORY."

17:39.475 --> 17:42.978
MEET WHERE?

17:43.437 --> 17:46.023
IN THE GYM.

17:57.367 --> 17:59.495
[SCREAMING]

18:04.583 --> 18:07.795
AH, THE POWER
OF THE PRESS.

18:10.214 --> 18:13.008
HELLO? HELLO?

18:13.091 --> 18:13.133
SHH!

18:16.595 --> 18:19.014
THE NAME IS DEEP WOLF.

18:26.105 --> 18:28.357
FOLLOW THE MAINTENANCE
BUDGET.

18:28.440 --> 18:29.441
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

18:29.525 --> 18:31.485
DO IT! I'VE GOT TO GET BACK
TO LIFE SCIENCE.

18:31.568 --> 18:34.029
I MEAN,
AN INFORMANTS CONVENTION.

18:34.112 --> 18:35.739
IF YOU NEED
ANY MORE INFORMATION,

18:35.823 --> 18:39.368
KNOCK 4 TIMES
ON ROOM 109.

18:42.329 --> 18:44.331
[CRASH]

18:46.458 --> 18:47.876
{\an1}HERE'S TOMORROW'S
"HOWLER" HOROSCOPE.

18:47.960 --> 18:50.712
THEY ALL SAY
THE SAME THING.

18:50.796 --> 18:54.967
"BRING COOKIE
A GIFT TODAY."

18:55.050 --> 18:57.010
{\an1}HEY, I'M THE SCHOOL
PSYCHIC REPORTER,

18:57.094 --> 19:00.556
AND THIS IS WHAT THE STARS
TELL ME TO WRITE.

19:00.639 --> 19:02.558
SO RUN IT.

19:07.813 --> 19:09.857
WHO GAVE YOU
THIS BUDGET?

19:09.940 --> 19:10.899
DEEP WOLF.

19:09.940 --> 19:10.899
DEEP WOLF.

19:10.983 --> 19:13.986
THIS IS CLASSIFIED.

19:14.069 --> 19:15.279
[LOUD WHIRRING]

19:15.362 --> 19:17.072
LET ME REPEAT--
WE WANT TO SEE THIS HAMSTER

19:17.155 --> 19:20.701
{\an1}ON THE FRONT PAGE
OF TOMORROW'S PAPER.

19:20.784 --> 19:23.245
RIGHT, MR. BURTON?

19:23.328 --> 19:25.664
NO, NO, NO. I WANT TO USE
THE EXPENSIVE TILES HERE.

19:25.747 --> 19:28.417
GREAT! HA HA HA.

19:28.500 --> 19:31.211
{\an1}I DON'T LIKE YOUR SUIT.
YOU NEED A NEW ONE.

19:34.923 --> 19:36.383
AAH!

19:40.971 --> 19:42.931
[KNOCK KNOCK KNOCK KNOCK]

19:43.015 --> 19:45.017
{\an1}COME IN.

19:45.809 --> 19:48.103
{\an1}DID YOU FOLLOW
THE BUDGET?

19:48.186 --> 19:49.104
CRUBBS TOOK IT.

19:49.187 --> 19:49.897
AND IT GOT
SHREDDED.

19:49.980 --> 19:52.274
{\an1}DON'T LET THEM KNOW
WHERE YOU GOT IT.

19:52.357 --> 19:55.611
IF ANYONE FINDS OUT
IT'S ME, I'M DEAD!

19:55.694 --> 19:57.779
SORRY.
I COULDN'T SEE.

19:57.863 --> 20:00.490
{\an1}LOOK, THE REPORT
FROM THE SCHOOL BOARD

20:00.574 --> 20:02.492
{\an1}STATES THAT
THE TILE REPAIRS

20:02.576 --> 20:04.161
{\an1}WERE PAID FOR
BUT NEVER DONE.

20:04.244 --> 20:07.247
{\an1}THAT LEAVES $20,000
UNACCOUNTED FOR.

20:07.331 --> 20:11.877
{\an1}SO, WHAT'S THE "HOWLER"
GOING TO DO ABOUT IT?

20:11.960 --> 20:16.506
{\an1}ALL RIGHT. IF WE RUN
"MEET MARMADUKE,"

20:16.590 --> 20:18.133
THE KIDS WILL MEET
MARMADUKE,

20:18.216 --> 20:19.468
BUT IF WE RUN TILE-GATE,

20:19.551 --> 20:22.429
WE'LL ALL GET BUSTED,
AND CRUBBS WILL FIRE MR. MONROE.

20:22.512 --> 20:24.014
{\an1}BUT THEY WON'T KNOW
THAT'S ME.

20:24.097 --> 20:26.516
{\an1}AND YOU ALL
WILL GET IN TROUBLE,

20:26.600 --> 20:30.437
{\an1}BUT THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS
TO GREAT NEWSPAPER PEOPLE.

20:35.067 --> 20:37.444
RUN IT.

20:41.240 --> 20:44.910
{\an1}OH, I'M REALLY GLAD YOU GUYS
DID THE RIGHT THING.

20:44.993 --> 20:46.203
AAH!

20:46.286 --> 20:47.329
WHY IS MY FACE
ON THE COVER?!

20:47.412 --> 20:50.791
SETH, MR. MONROE WAS SUPPOSED
TO BE AN UNNAMED SOURCE.

20:50.874 --> 20:53.502
OH. I DIDN'T
NAME HIM.

20:53.585 --> 20:55.504
I JUST PRINTED
HIS PICTURE.

20:55.587 --> 20:57.506
THE OTHER ONE
WAS SO DARK.

20:57.589 --> 20:58.924
THAT WAS THE POINT!

20:59.007 --> 21:00.717
{\an1}OK, IF ANYBODY
NEEDS ME,

21:00.801 --> 21:02.719
{\an1}I'LL BE LIVING
WITH THE PENGUINS.

21:02.803 --> 21:04.680
NO! WE CAN'T
LET THAT HAPPEN.

21:04.763 --> 21:05.430
SETH, HOW MANY PAPERS
DID YOU PRINT?

21:05.514 --> 21:07.557
12.

21:07.641 --> 21:11.478
NO, WAIT. 400.

21:12.646 --> 21:14.856
{\an1}OK. WE HAVE TO
GET THEM ALL BACK,

21:14.940 --> 21:16.400
{\an1}CHANGE THE PHOTO,
AND RUN A LATE EDITION.

21:16.483 --> 21:18.610
DON'T LET ANYONE
SEE THAT PICTURE.

21:19.695 --> 21:20.821
GO!

21:31.873 --> 21:32.749
HIYAH!

21:32.833 --> 21:33.792
WHOO-HOO.

21:33.875 --> 21:36.211
WAH!

21:36.628 --> 21:39.548
397, 398, 399!

21:39.631 --> 21:41.133
WHERE'S THE LAST ONE?

21:41.216 --> 21:45.554
GRAB IT! GRAB
THE PAPER! AH, AH!

21:45.637 --> 21:48.140
[SHOUTING]

21:54.146 --> 21:57.441
{\an1}I DON'T BELIEVE IT!
I AM OUTRAGED!

21:57.524 --> 21:59.151
I KNOW. WE'RE DEAD.

21:59.234 --> 22:01.611
{\an1}NO. I CAN'T BELIEVE
THERE'S $20,000 MISSING

22:01.695 --> 22:03.071
FROM THE MAINTENANCE
BUDGET. IS THIS TRUE?

22:03.155 --> 22:04.948
CRUBBS, I WANT
THESE SHREDDED.

22:05.032 --> 22:09.411
I WANT ALL OF THEM
EXPELLED.

22:09.494 --> 22:10.495
[LOUD WHIRRING]

22:10.579 --> 22:12.456
AND I WANT THIS
SHREDDED, TOO.

22:17.336 --> 22:19.087
THE NEW ADDITION
YOU'RE BUILDING

22:19.171 --> 22:20.922
IS A POOL
IN YOUR BACKYARD?

22:21.006 --> 22:21.923
{\an1}Man: YEAH.

22:22.007 --> 22:23.759
{\an5}THE WHOLE THING'S
GOING TO COST
ABOUT 20 GRAND,

22:23.842 --> 22:26.303
{\an5}NOW THAT
WE'RE GOING WITH
THE EXPENSIVE TILES.

22:26.386 --> 22:30.974
{\an1}WE NEED CEILING TILES,
AND YOU BOUGHT POOL TILES?

22:31.058 --> 22:33.101
HA HA HA. I WAS JUST
BORROWING THE MONEY.

22:33.185 --> 22:35.896
{\an1}AND I WOULD HAVE
GOT AWAY WITH IT, TOO,

22:35.979 --> 22:38.273
{\an1}IF IT WEREN'T FOR
THOSE MEDDLING KIDS.

22:38.356 --> 22:38.940
AND NOW YOU'LL HAVE TO
DEAL WITH ME

22:39.024 --> 22:42.152
AND PROBABLY A LAWYER.

22:42.235 --> 22:43.570
AND AS FOR YOU GUYS,

22:43.653 --> 22:47.449
I THINK YOU GOT THE HEADLINE
FOR YOUR LATE EDITION.

22:47.532 --> 22:49.743
[STUDENTS CHEERING]

22:53.705 --> 22:55.248
{\an1}I LIKE BEING
A NEWSPAPERMAN.

22:55.332 --> 22:58.835
AND I LIKE BEING
A HOROSCOPE WRITER.

22:58.919 --> 23:01.338
I'M A GEMINI, AND I GOT COOKIE
THIS AUTOGRAPHED BASEBALL BAT.

23:01.421 --> 23:03.298
{\an5}I GOT HIM NEW
GARDENING TOOLS,
BUT I'M A VIRGO.

23:03.381 --> 23:05.425
I'M AN ARIES.
I GOT HIM THIS MACE.

23:07.219 --> 23:09.179
WAIT. THESE ALL SAY
THE SAME THING!

23:09.262 --> 23:12.099
{\an1}WHO WRITES THESE
HOROSCOPES, ANYWAY?

23:12.182 --> 23:15.185
OH. COOK DOES.

23:21.733 --> 23:24.152
UH! I'M GONNA RUN NOW.

23:24.236 --> 23:25.320
AAH!

23:25.403 --> 23:26.613
[SHOUTING]

23:27.572 --> 23:29.783
AAH!

23:29.866 --> 23:31.910
LOOKS LIKE WE HAVE
OUR NEXT HEADLINE.

23:31.993 --> 23:34.746
[SCREAMING]

23:34.830 --> 23:36.081
{\an8}SORRY.

23:36.164 --> 23:38.500
{\an7}HA HA HA!

23:38.583 --> 23:40.085
{\an8}HA HA HA!

23:40.168 --> 23:42.504
{\an8}OH, GOD. HA HA HA.

23:42.587 --> 23:44.673
{\an8}TILE WORKS WERE--

23:44.756 --> 23:46.341
{\an8}THE REPORTS FROM THE--

23:46.424 --> 23:49.219
{\an8}THE REPORTS
FROM SCHOOL BOARD SAID--

23:49.302 --> 23:49.761
{\an8}HA HA HA HA!

23:49.845 --> 23:54.349
{\an8}AAH! AAH!

23:54.432 --> 23:57.102
{\an8}YOU DON'T SEE THE NEED
FOR YOU TO DO...

23:57.185 --> 23:59.813
{\an7}ONE SPRING-FEVER
KISS CAKE KEYS CAKE...

24:02.190 --> 24:06.069
{\an8}OH! MY NIPPLES! OW!

24:06.153 --> 24:09.156
